<br>
<br>
1. Damage - I'm satisfied with our damage for now. As long as we have endurance to style with we tend to do very well. I wouldn't mind seeing a slight increase in our base damage for those times when we run out of endurance, but I think we'll be ok without it.<br>
<br>
2. I would like to see something to make us more group friendly come from speccing in Parry. Perhaps something similar to Guard in the sheild spec, although not quite as powerful. Different levels could be earned at 10, 20, 30 and 40 spec.<br>
<br>
3. Increased run speed (5-10%) for charge and while in frenzy. With the fairly common availablility of end regen in all 3 realms, this would allow us a better chance to catch that fleeing opponent when they turn and sprint away from us.<br>
<br>
4. Our Unique realm ability stle, Tundra, needs serious improvement. I can't even begin to describe how disgusted the Zerker community is about having an unique RA style that gets a penalty for dual weilding. Did I mention that Zerkers are the dual weilding melee class of Midgard?<br>
<br>
5. The level 50 LA style, Aurora Borealis, should be a follow up, positional based or based off of US parrying, not us being parried. If it were made into a follow up style, it could be based off of Doublefrost. If that would be seen as too overpowering, how about making it the 3rd style in the parry or evade chain? If that wouldn't work, how about making it a parry opening. Our current parry opening style is level 8, so this would give us a nice upgrade option. Side or front positional would also be an improvement.<br>
<br>
6. Would like to see the Strength cap removed and replaced with a diminishing returns system. Even races that start with a low Strength stat can reach or come close to the current cap so there is no advantage to playing a race with a high natural Strength. This system could also be applied to every other stat, giving the players the choice of how they want to customize their char.<br>
<br>
7. Full implementation of shape shifting. Many Zerks don't like turning into a vendo when we use our Frenzy ability. It highlights us on the battlefield, and the added damage ability just doesn't make up for the defensive loss at high levels. I would like to see full shape changing implemented, whether it is a part of frenzy or it is a seperate ability.<br>
<br>
8. Make frenzy more usefull/desirable:<br>
a. Gain resists at each level of frenzy. Possibly gain a small percentage of resists at each level of frenzy. This could be a depiction of the berserker not feeling the damage his enemies inflict while he is in an altered form.<br>
b. Return defensive abilities at each level of frenzy. Perhaps let us have a very reduced ability to evade and/or parry as we gain levels in Frenzy.<br>
<br>
9. Make sure the effects from LA styles are not being broken by the strike of the off hand. The only effects we know are working are the bleeds and the stun from Frosty Gaze. The styles that slow or hinder don't seem to be having any effect or the effect is being broken by the hit of the left axe.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
In summary, I think the Berserker is a very solid class. We are able to PvE with relative ease and acceptable down time. When we RvR our biggest challenge is getting into melee range. Once into melee range, we do excellent damage to casters and good damage to other classes. As is always the case, there are exceptions. Players who have built up a LOT of resistance to melee damage can reduce us to mere annoyances. On the other hand, if specced and buffed to an extreme, berserkers can do insane damage to our enemies in a very short amount of time. The goal should be to focus on the average, and try to bring the extremes closer together.<br>
 <p>-Robb<br>
